quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  42,16,"As for those who dispute about Allah after He is Ë¹alreadyËº acknowledged Ë¹by manyËº, their argument is futile in the sight of their Lord. Upon them is wrath, and they will suffer a severe punishment"
  42,17,"It is Allah Who has revealed the Book with the truth and the balance Ë¹of justiceËº. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near"
  42,18,"Those who disbelieve in it Ë¹ask toËº hasten it Ë¹mockinglyËº. But the believers are fearful of it, knowing that it is the truth. Surely those who dispute about the Hour have gone far astray"
  42,19,"Allah is Ever Kind to His servants. He provides Ë¹abundantlyËº to whoever He wills. And He is the All-Powerful, Almighty"
  42,20,"Whoever desires the harvest of the Hereafter, We will increase their harvest. And whoever desires Ë¹onlyËº the harvest of this world, We will give them some of it, but they will have no share in the Hereafter"
  42,21,"Or do they have associate-gods who have ordained for them some Ë¹polytheisticËº beliefs, which Allah has not authorized? Had it not been for Ë¹priorËº decree on Judgment, the matter would have certainly been settled between them Ë¹at onceËº. And surely the wrongdoers will suffer a painful punishment"
  42,22,"You will see the wrongdoers fearful Ë¹of the punishmentËº for what they committed but it will be inevitable for them, whereas those who believe and do good will be in the lush Gardens of Paradise. They will have whatever they desire from their Lord. That is Ë¹trulyËº the greatest bounty"